import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Miles_per_Gallon'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.title('How has the Miles_per_Gallon changed over the years?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
